 793+ 9125              ; ============================================
 794+ 9125              ; ensureCommandMode
 795+ 9125              ;   Best-effort attempt to ensure the ESP is in AT command mode.
 796+ 9125              ;   1) Send AT and expect OK.
 797+ 9125              ;   2) If not OK, send escape sequence +++ with guard times and retry AT.
 798+ 9125              ;
 799+ 9125              ;   Returns: CF=0 if OK received, CF=1 otherwise.
 800+ 9125              ;
 801+ 9125              ;   Notes:
 802+ 9125              ;   - Mutes UART byte-log while sending raw +++/CRLF to avoid polluting the UART log buffer.
